# UI Design and Styling Standards

## Tailwind CSS Conventions

### Utility Class Order
Follow this consistent order for Tailwind classes:
1. Layout (display, position, flex, grid)
2. Sizing (width, height, min/max)
3. Spacing (margin, padding, gap)
4. Typography (font, text, line-height)
5. Borders (border, rounded)
6. Background (bg)
7. Effects (shadow, opacity)
8. Transitions/Animations
9. Responsive variants
10. State variants (hover, focus, dark)

```tsx
// Good example
<div className="flex items-center justify-between w-full px-6 py-4 text-lg font-bold bg-surface border-b shadow-sm hover:bg-muted dark:bg-card">
```

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Use Tailwind breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Test on both mobile and desktop viewports

```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
```

## Color Palette and Theme

### Theme Variables
Use CSS custom properties defined in `index.css`:

```typescript
// Light/Dark mode support via next-themes
const colorVariables = {
  // Base colors
  background: 'hsl(var(--background))',
  foreground: 'hsl(var(--foreground))',
  
  // Component colors
  card: 'hsl(var(--card))',
  surface: 'hsl(var(--surface))',
  
  // Semantic colors
  primary: 'hsl(var(--primary))',
  destructive: 'hsl(var(--destructive))',
  success: 'hsl(var(--success))',
  warning: 'hsl(var(--warning))',
  
  // Text colors
  'muted-foreground': 'hsl(var(--muted-foreground))',
};
```

### Color Usage Patterns

**Backgrounds**:
```tsx
<div className="bg-background">      {/* Page background */}
<div className="bg-surface">         {/* Elevated surface */}
<div className="bg-card">            {/* Card background */}
<div className="bg-muted">           {/* Muted/secondary bg */}
```

**Text Colors**:
```tsx
<h1 className="text-foreground">     {/* Primary text */}
<p className="text-muted-foreground"> {/* Secondary text */}
<span className="text-primary">      {/* Branded text */}
<span className="text-destructive">  {/* Error/danger text */}
```

**Theme-Aware Dark Mode**:
```tsx
// Automatically adapts via CSS variables - preferred
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">

// Manual dark mode override - only when needed
<div className="bg-blue-500 dark:bg-blue-700">
```

## Variant Styles Pattern

For components with multiple visual variants, use the established pattern:

```typescript
// Define variant type
export type Variant = 'default' | 'primary' | 'success' | 'warning' | 'info';

// Define variant styles Record
export const variantStyles: Record<
  Variant,
  {
    card: string;
    icon: string;
    text: string;
    badge: string;
    hover: string;
  }
> = {
  default: {
    card: 'bg-card',
    icon: 'bg-muted text-muted-foreground',
    text: 'text-foreground',
    badge: 'bg-muted text-muted-foreground',
    hover: 'hover:bg-muted/40',
  },
  primary: {
    card: 'bg-primary/15 dark:bg-primary/10',
    icon: 'bg-primary/20 text-primary',
    text: 'text-primary',
    badge: 'bg-primary/20 text-primary',
    hover: 'hover:bg-primary/25 dark:hover:bg-primary/20',
  },
  success: {
    card: 'bg-emerald-500/15 dark:bg-emerald-500/10',
    icon: 'bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-500',
    text: 'text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400',
    badge: 'bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400',
    hover: 'hover:bg-emerald-500/25 dark:hover:bg-emerald-500/20',
  },
  warning: {
    card: 'bg-orange-500/15 dark:bg-orange-500/10',
    icon: 'bg-orange-500/20 text-orange-500',
    text: 'text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400',
    badge: 'bg-orange-500/20 text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400',
    hover: 'hover:bg-orange-500/25 dark:hover:bg-orange-500/20',
  },
  info: {
    card: 'bg-blue-500/15 dark:bg-blue-500/10',
    icon: 'bg-blue-500/20 text-blue-500',
    text: 'text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400',
    badge: 'bg-blue-500/20 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400',
    hover: 'hover:bg-blue-500/25 dark:hover:bg-blue-500/20',
  },
};

// Usage in component
interface StatsCardProps {
  variant?: Variant;
}

const StatsCard = ({ variant = 'default' }: StatsCardProps) => {
  const styles = variantStyles[variant];
  
  return (
    <div className={cn(styles.card, styles.hover, 'p-6 rounded-lg')}>
      <div className={cn(styles.icon, 'p-3 rounded-full')}>
        <Icon />
      </div>
      <p className={styles.text}>Content</p>
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Icon Usage

### Lucide React Icons
Primary icon library. Use for UI elements:

```tsx
import { Search, User, Settings, ChevronDown } from 'lucide-react';

<Search className="size-5 text-muted-foreground" />
<User className="size-4" />
```

### Material Symbols
Used for specific app iconography:

```tsx
{/* Filled variant */}
<span className="material-symbols-outlined text-2xl">flood</span>
<span className="material-symbols-outlined text-sm">arrow_forward</span>

{/* Outlined variant - default */}
<span className="material-symbols-outlined">settings</span>
```

**Icon Sizing**:
- `size-4` (16px) - Small inline icons
- `size-5` (20px) - Standard UI icons
- `size-6` (24px) - Large UI icons
- `size-8` (32px) - Feature icons
- `text-sm/base/lg/xl/2xl` for Material Symbols

